The `supabase-migration.sql` file already has exactly what you need. Run this in your Supabase SQL editor (**Project → SQL Editor → New query**):

```sql
-- Add new columns for author, article metadata, and podcast metadata
ALTER TABLE books ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS author text;
ALTER TABLE books ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS publication text;
ALTER TABLE books ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS article_date text;
ALTER TABLE books ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS show_title text;
ALTER TABLE books ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS guests text;
ALTER TABLE books ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS air_date text;

-- Update the type check constraint to include 'podcast'
ALTER TABLE books DROP CONSTRAINT IF EXISTS books_type_check;
ALTER TABLE books ADD CONSTRAINT books_type_check
  CHECK (type IN ('book', 'article', 'podcast'));
```

One note on `episode_title`: podcast episode titles are stored in the existing `title` column, so no new column is needed for that — the 6 columns above cover everything.

After running the migration, your PATCH saves should work correctly. The error handling added to `DetailModal` will show an inline error message if anything still fails.

